Data Analyst Job Market Analysis

Introduction

This report analyzes the job market for data analysts in the United States. It examines the relationship between years of experience and salary, as well as the distribution of salaries by programming language.

Data Cleaning

The data was cleaned to remove columns with only one unique value and to combine all SQL variants into one category.

Conclusion

The data analysis shows: A positive correlation between years of experience and salary. Different salary distributions across programming languages. SQL appears to be the most commonly requested language (145 postings)
